The paper analyzes the relationship between social media attention and article visitors directed by social media, which falls under the category of social media and its impact on scholarly articles. This could be categorized under several sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SD (Software Development and Programming Languages). However, given the focus on social media and its impact on scholarly articles, cs.SI is the most likely sub-category.
